  "intent": "Explain the end-to-end funnel that turns a user's topic request into rows of `.regin/topics/topic.json`: an external tool-using agent drafts per-topic JSON + wiki, regin validates and persists it ORM-first through the proposal ORM, the agent self-ingests via a notify-on-finish command in its own process (capturing its real drafting-session trace id and firing an inbox `proposal.ready` card), reviewers iterate via regenerate/restore/feedback/review-state (with scoped content-drift regenerate that splices only drifted topics and keeps untouched wikis byte-identical), and a single server-side /diff + /apply path (or the legacy accept/replace/merge/ignore helpers) promotes a topic into the approved graph. Also covers the two orthogonal status axes (run lifecycle vs review state), the agentic review-note reviewer, the cross-thread cancel machinery that lets Stop terminate the agent subprocess, and the reaper that fails runs orphaned by a serve restart.",
  "label": "Topic proposal pipeline (request \u2192 draft \u2192 review \u2192 apply/stop)",
